<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Solving auto on absolutely positioned non-replaced elements with rtl direction</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#the-width-property" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="When 'left' and 'right' are 'auto', 'width' is not 'auto', and 'direction' is 'rtl', 'right' is set to static position." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #div1
            {
                border: solid;
                direction: rtl;
                height: 3in;
                position: relative;
                width: 3in;
            }
            div div
            {
                background-color: orange;
                height: 1in;
                left: auto;
                position: absolute;
                right: auto;
                width: 1in;
            }
            p
            {
                direction: ltr;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the orange box below is directly below the "Filler Text" and is aligned against the right side of the black box.</p>
        <div id="div1">
            Filler Text
            <div></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>